WEBVTT

00:02.753 --> 00:05.129
We cannot divulge
specifics, but what we can tell you

00:05.130 --> 00:08.300
is that we are preparing
for a massive catastrophe

00:09.134 --> 00:11.135
that could cause an extinction-level event
for humanity

00:11.136 --> 00:13.387
in the very near, very real future.

00:17.100 --> 00:20.020
Listen, I know this all
sounds pretty far-fetched.

00:20.771 --> 00:23.231
But you know when it
won't seem far-fetched?

00:23.232 --> 00:25.525
In less than a decade, when a tsunami

00:25.526 --> 00:28.820
plunges the entire eastern seaboard
of the United States underwater.

00:29.905 --> 00:31.197
Marsha, you wanna come in here?

00:31.198 --> 00:33.699
Xavier's gonna take me on a little walk.

00:33.700 --> 00:36.077
The minute Versailles
is called, you record the speech,

00:36.078 --> 00:38.579
we're escorted down, wait for confirmation

00:38.580 --> 00:41.582
of the safest route
to Joint Base Andrews, then we're out.

00:41.583 --> 00:44.336
Collins, I think it's time you put
your foot down with your wife.

00:44.962 --> 00:48.590
Trips to Atlanta are not as risk-free
as they used to be.

00:49.174 --> 00:52.009
My wife hasn't listened to me
for 20 years, sir.

00:52.010 --> 00:54.554
I guess we'll just have
to go pick her up from there.

00:55.514 --> 00:56.515
Don't go.

00:57.516 --> 00:58.642
I love you, baby.

01:02.521 --> 01:04.022
See you in 10 days.

01:06.441 --> 01:08.569
Your wife is alive out there, Xavier.

01:09.820 --> 01:11.572
And if you stop all this nonsense...

01:13.323 --> 01:14.700
I can help you find her.

01:21.582 --> 01:24.710
 <i>And now, Bill Roberts
reporting from the United Nations.</i>

01:25.794 --> 01:28.588
 <i>The curtain goes up
in what is hoped to be the final act</i>

01:28.589 --> 01:33.009
<i>of the nearly two-week-long drama
that is the Cuban Missile Crisis.</i>

01:33.010 --> 01:34.719
<i>Today, Ambassador Adlai Stevenson</i>

01:34.720 --> 01:36.972
<i>addressed the United Nations
Security Council.</i>

01:37.848 --> 01:40.891
 <i>This resolution calls
as an interim measure</i>

01:40.892 --> 01:45.187
<i>under Article 40 of the charter
for the immediate dismantling</i>

01:45.188 --> 01:50.067
<i>and withdrawal from Cuba of all missile
and other offensive weapons.</i>

01:50.068 --> 01:53.237
<i>Leaders around the world
rejoiced as a peaceful solution...</i>

02:00.120 --> 02:01.371
I didn't know you'd come home.

02:01.872 --> 02:03.998
We got intelligence an hour ago.

02:03.999 --> 02:07.836
The Soviet sub that was loaded with nukes
was out of contact with Moscow.

02:09.588 --> 02:11.297
The one that turned around?

02:11.298 --> 02:14.760
Apparently, its last orders
were to launch all missiles if cornered.

02:15.844 --> 02:19.806
The captain made the decision not to,
on his own.

02:20.932 --> 02:22.017
Jesus.

02:29.524 --> 02:33.320
It's gonna happen again, Miriam.
It's goddamn inevitable.

02:40.327 --> 02:43.080
What if the wrong person's
at the controls next time?

02:45.207 --> 02:47.834
What if the wrong person
decides not to turn around?

02:50.045 --> 02:51.254
You're tired.

02:53.048 --> 02:54.174
Come to bed.

02:58.470 --> 03:01.223
You can't save the world tonight.

03:04.726 --> 03:07.062
Okay. Okay.

03:54.776 --> 03:55.777
Didn't you hear what I said?

03:57.988 --> 03:59.865
- Your wife is alive.
- Bullshit.

04:00.824 --> 04:01.824
I'm not playing your games.

04:01.825 --> 04:04.286
- It's not bullshit, Agent Collins.
- Everything was destroyed.

04:05.370 --> 04:06.620
It's a nuclear winter out there.

04:06.621 --> 04:09.040
Which is exactly
what we thought, initially.

04:10.041 --> 04:12.669
The expedition,
the four that didn't return.

04:15.088 --> 04:16.714
They didn't die
because of the environment.

04:16.715 --> 04:20.135
They died because they were bringing
a survivor back to the bunker.

04:21.178 --> 04:24.472
Which I ordered them
not to do, by the way.

04:24.473 --> 04:26.056
And it was gonna open
a whole can of worms,

04:26.057 --> 04:27.476
and so I had to take care of them.

04:29.060 --> 04:31.563
My God, could I sound
any more like a Bond villain?

04:32.981 --> 04:34.899
I swear I'm not a monster.

04:34.900 --> 04:38.236
Interesting how people who swear
they aren't monsters usually are.

04:46.161 --> 04:48.746
The expedition set up
shortwave transmitters

04:48.747 --> 04:51.082
so that we could communicate
while they were outside.

04:52.542 --> 04:54.794
Transmitters are still active,
and I've been listening.

04:54.795 --> 04:57.004
<i>My name is Cameron Middleton</i>

04:57.005 --> 04:58.798
<i>of Zanesville, Ohio.</i>

04:58.799 --> 05:01.592
<i>If Carla or Joseph Middleton
are listening,</i>

05:01.593 --> 05:04.053
<i>please tell them I'm headed
for the Colorado Bunker Com--</i>

05:05.764 --> 05:08.098
<i>Looking for safe passages to Colorado.</i>

05:08.099 --> 05:11.101
<i>Western Kansas is irradiated.</i>

05:11.102 --> 05:13.729
<i>Forming a community south of Paso Robles.</i>

05:13.730 --> 05:15.981
<i>If you're listening, several members
plan to set up camp there.</i>

05:18.276 --> 05:19.486
People are alive.

05:22.197 --> 05:24.950
And they're looking for us,
and I believe your wife is one of them.

05:28.245 --> 05:31.205
Don't... Don't you fucking dare.

05:31.206 --> 05:34.626
She was in Atlanta, it was a direct hit.
It was unsurvivable.

05:36.127 --> 05:38.212
The president did something that day,
Agent Collins.

05:38.213 --> 05:40.632
- Something you don't know about.
- Not true, I was with him.

05:41.132 --> 05:44.051
I was with him that whole
fucking horrible day.

05:44.052 --> 05:46.763
- You don't know everything that happened.
- I was there!

05:49.182 --> 05:50.267
I was there.

05:51.309 --> 05:53.686
[on TV] <i>This is our
continuing coverage of the situation</i>

05:53.687 --> 05:57.439
<i>that started in Antarctica
and is causing unprecedented destruction</i>

05:57.440 --> 05:59.567
<i>and chaos around the globe.</i>

05:59.568 --> 06:03.779
<i>Here's what we do know right now.
Just over three hours ago,</i>

06:03.780 --> 06:06.782
<i>what scientists are calling
a massive mega-caldera,</i>

06:06.783 --> 06:10.744
<i>or super volcano,
erupted under the Antarctic ice sheet,</i>

06:10.745 --> 06:13.998
<i>expelling millions of tons of ash
into the atmosphere.</i>

06:13.999 --> 06:18.002
<i>The force of the explosion
shattered large portions</i>

06:18.003 --> 06:22.715
<i>of the ice shelf, instantly melting
trillions of gallons of water</i>

06:22.716 --> 06:26.135
<i>and triggering a tsunami
that is hurdling northward</i>

06:26.136 --> 06:29.139
<i>at nearly 600 miles an hour.</i>

06:30.056 --> 06:31.557
<i>Most disturbingly, some reports...</i>

06:31.558 --> 06:35.478
<i>...indicate the wave
may be as high as 300 feet.</i>

06:36.229 --> 06:37.396
<i>In an unprecedented move,</i>

06:37.397 --> 06:40.107
<i>the National Oceanic
and Atmospheric Administration</i>

06:40.108 --> 06:44.153
<i>has put all coastal areas
of the United States on a tsunami watch</i>

06:44.154 --> 06:48.949
<i>with estimated landfall
at Key West in two hours,</i>

06:48.950 --> 06:51.661
<i>and the nation's capital in five.</i>

06:52.537 --> 06:54.330
-  Xavier?
-  [on TV] <i>Adding to the chaos</i>

06:54.331 --> 06:56.206
<i>and the confusion
is a stock market in freefall...</i>

06:56.207 --> 06:58.208
Xavier, did you hear that?
D.C. in five hours.

06:58.209 --> 06:59.835
<i>Nationwide cell phone
and internet outages...</i>

06:59.836 --> 07:01.003
- Xavier.
- Hm?

07:01.004 --> 07:02.713
<i>...as networks are overrun...</i>

07:02.714 --> 07:04.757
Are you guys here because of this?

07:04.758 --> 07:07.259
Why are you two stationed
outside the cabinet room door?

07:07.260 --> 07:09.553
Don't ask me, ma'am.
This is my third day here.

07:09.554 --> 07:12.681
Uh, is this not normal, sir?

07:12.682 --> 07:16.060
Marsha, we're just doing what we're told.
I have no additional information.

07:16.061 --> 07:18.896
-  That's Melbourne?
-  <i>The death toll</i>

07:18.897 --> 07:20.689
<i>-is expected to be in the hundreds...
- Nancy's family lives there.</i>

07:20.690 --> 07:22.608
<i>Ashbridge Preparatory.</i>

07:22.609 --> 07:24.401
Can you give me 20 seconds?

07:24.402 --> 07:27.196
Hi, Denise, this is Xavier Collins again.
I'm just calling to reiterate--

07:27.197 --> 07:29.198
-  <i>We're a little busy, Xavier.
- No, I know. I know.</i>

07:29.199 --> 07:32.660
But how important it is that James
and Presley stay near Jeremy Bradford.

07:32.661 --> 07:35.871
-  <i>You told me this before.
- I know. I'm sorry.</i>

07:35.872 --> 07:37.498
But someone will be coming to get them.

07:37.499 --> 07:39.750
You know, actually, if you could just
give them their phones so I could talk.

07:39.751 --> 07:42.337
- Calls keep dropping.
-  <i>Goodbye, Mr. Collins.</i>

07:43.129 --> 07:44.421
Fuck!

07:44.422 --> 07:46.423
<i>And what is especially alarming...</i>

07:46.424 --> 07:47.966
- Xavier, talk to me.
- Hm.

07:47.967 --> 07:49.843
What do you know?
The cabinet gathered

07:49.844 --> 07:53.639
like there's some kind of plan in motion,
and I heard the word "Versailles."

07:53.640 --> 07:55.517
Marsha, I swear I would tell you.

07:56.434 --> 07:59.353
I mean, do I need to pick
Edward up from daycare?

07:59.354 --> 08:01.271
He's got health issues.

08:01.272 --> 08:02.564
Talk to him.

08:02.565 --> 08:05.694
The-- the president, I have been
with him since his Senate campaign.

08:06.736 --> 08:08.904
- Edward can't be left alone, okay?
- I will talk to him.

08:08.905 --> 08:10.489
I will tell you everything
that I find out.

08:10.490 --> 08:12.908
Out of the way. VP coming through.

08:15.787 --> 08:18.163
- Classified!
- Sorry, sir.

08:18.164 --> 08:20.582
Mr. Vice President,
I need a moment with the president

08:20.583 --> 08:22.376
- if you don't--
- You're kidding me.

08:22.377 --> 08:23.669
...communication with our--

08:23.670 --> 08:26.296
Russia's gone dark. Completely dark.

08:26.297 --> 08:29.007
Thank you, Henry, we know.
Why don't you have a seat?

08:29.008 --> 08:30.885
Take a breather, and maybe a Valium.

08:32.011 --> 08:33.722
Joint Chiefs were just
walking us through it.

08:34.723 --> 08:36.974
- General Curtleigh.
- Yes, sir.

08:36.975 --> 08:41.520
As the vice president noted,
Russia isn't picking up the red line.

08:41.521 --> 08:42.813
We're still trying to confirm

08:42.814 --> 08:45.107
if the Svoboda Group coup d'etat
was successful.

08:45.108 --> 08:48.445
- Indications are that it was.
- CIA can confirm that.

08:49.946 --> 08:51.780
We also have confirmations
of troop mobilization

08:51.781 --> 08:54.658
to the Chinese border
along the Argun and Amur Rivers

08:54.659 --> 08:56.201
and Western Mongolia.

08:56.202 --> 08:58.495
It feels like they're setting up
for a land grab, sir.

08:58.496 --> 09:02.166
And since we don't know all the players
except for the Svoboda Group leader--

09:02.167 --> 09:03.917
Cherkin. Unpredictable.

09:03.918 --> 09:05.754
- Ruthless.
- Which I was about to say.

09:07.297 --> 09:09.840
It is the recommendation
of the Joint Chiefs of Staff

09:09.841 --> 09:11.633
that we move to DEFCON 3.

09:11.634 --> 09:14.596
This will set the Air Force
readiness envelope to 15 minutes.

09:15.346 --> 09:17.639
Christ. Okay, anything else?

09:17.640 --> 09:20.350
The UN Security Council
is convening in two hours.

09:20.351 --> 09:21.977
NATO countries have been reaching out.

09:21.978 --> 09:24.355
Two hours. We lose Florida in two hours!

09:25.023 --> 09:27.525
I've said that before,
but it was about the electoral college.

09:29.110 --> 09:30.111
Okay.

09:31.488 --> 09:32.906
I mean, how bad is it?

09:33.907 --> 09:35.282
I wanna know. I mean, I know it's bad.

09:35.283 --> 09:38.160
But honestly, is this it? Is it?

09:38.161 --> 09:39.536
Half the world leaders we're talking to

09:39.537 --> 09:41.205
say it's the end of the world,
the others don't.

09:41.206 --> 09:44.041
The Tories in England
say the volcano's too far away

09:44.042 --> 09:46.251
for them to be affected by it,
and they live on a fucking island.

09:46.252 --> 09:48.879
It will most certainly affect them, sir.

09:48.880 --> 09:52.591
This appears to be it, Mr. President.
It's what we've been preparing for.

09:52.592 --> 09:54.927
What about Australia?
Anyone on the horn with Melbourne?

09:54.928 --> 09:56.221
I can't get anything.

09:57.388 --> 10:00.141
Melbourne is gone. Sorry, Henry.

10:01.601 --> 10:03.269
Nancy's entire family.

10:03.978 --> 10:06.606
As is Sydney. All coastal cities.

10:07.607 --> 10:08.982
New Zealand, gone.

10:08.983 --> 10:11.985
Argentina, apart from
the mountain regions, effectively gone.

10:11.986 --> 10:14.822
Chile, South Africa. Need I go on?

10:16.366 --> 10:18.326
- We need to make the call.
- Okay, where are my nerds?

10:19.327 --> 10:21.703
Scientists, come on, step to.

10:21.704 --> 10:23.331
You said we'd have warning!

10:24.916 --> 10:26.708
Days or weeks, if this was the real thing.

10:26.709 --> 10:28.085
What the fuck happened?

10:28.086 --> 10:30.796
Mr. President,
we thought we'd have warning,

10:30.797 --> 10:32.756
but this happened faster
than the worst-case scenario

10:32.757 --> 10:34.550
- in all of our modeling.
-  Bunch of bullshit.

10:34.551 --> 10:36.927
- Come on.
- We calculated that there'd be 10 days

10:36.928 --> 10:38.595
from first seismic activity to eruption,

10:38.596 --> 10:40.597
but we had minutes.

10:40.598 --> 10:43.016
-  Sir!
- We are not making the wrong call here.

10:49.399 --> 10:50.733
Move us to DEFCON 3.

10:51.776 --> 10:53.402
Around the horn,
go or no go for Versailles.

10:53.403 --> 10:54.903
-  Joint Chiefs.
-  Go.

10:54.904 --> 10:56.321
-  Homeland Security.
-  Go.

10:56.322 --> 10:58.365
Jesus Christ, we know our fucking titles,
just give me your answers.

10:58.366 --> 11:05.455
Go.

11:08.877 --> 11:09.961
Okay.

11:11.087 --> 11:12.380
I'm calling Versailles.

11:13.840 --> 11:17.968
<i>So, right now, a-- a large wave
is-- is approaching Ind-Indonesia.</i>

11:17.969 --> 11:21.180
<i>Soon, it'll head
to the southern coast of India.</i>

11:21.181 --> 11:23.683
<i>So, Dr. Louge,
when do you think this will stop?</i>

11:25.268 --> 11:26.436
<i>When it's done.</i>

11:27.145 --> 11:30.480
<i>After rolling up to the North Pole
and echoing back down to Antarctica,</i>

11:30.481 --> 11:32.316
<i>maybe a dozen more times.</i>

11:32.317 --> 11:34.401
<i>Anything under 300 feet above sea level</i>

11:34.402 --> 11:36.445
<i>will be inundated.</i>

11:36.446 --> 11:38.947
<i>- You're not thinking about this correctly.
- Oh, my God.</i>

11:38.948 --> 11:40.782
[on TV] <i>It's not a wave.</i>

11:40.783 --> 11:42.951
<i>- The Antarctic ice sheet accounts...
-  Marsha.</i>

11:42.952 --> 11:44.870
My family's gonna be calling,
make sure you put them through.

11:44.871 --> 11:47.331
-  Yes, Mr. President.
- Sir, can I have a minute?

11:47.332 --> 11:49.167
It's a go for Versailles.

11:51.169 --> 11:53.171
Ryan, on me.

11:53.922 --> 11:57.217
<i>So, when it's done,
that's when it will end.</i>

12:01.763 --> 12:04.556
[over tablet] <i>Rumors of the
billionaire bunker complex in Colorado</i>

12:04.557 --> 12:06.475
<i>- continue to rise...
-  Priority list only.</i>

12:08.394 --> 12:09.978
Are they taking down paintings?

12:09.979 --> 12:13.190
Boss, what the hell is Versailles?
Is there anything I need to do?

12:13.191 --> 12:16.568
Your job as briefed.
I'm on Wildcat, you're on me.

12:16.569 --> 12:18.487
- Mr. President.
- Gotta get this tie off me.

12:18.488 --> 12:20.405
It's too fucking cheerful.

12:20.406 --> 12:22.741
-  <i>Hi, this is Dr. Teri--
- You know, I once read that neckties</i>

12:22.742 --> 12:25.619
date back to Serbian mercenaries
in the 1600s or some shit.

12:25.620 --> 12:27.497
Just do your job. Alright?
See if you can find...

12:31.834 --> 12:35.421
Okay, let's go blue.
It's a little more calming.

12:40.551 --> 12:42.470
Alright, steps, what's next?
Walk me through it.

12:44.013 --> 12:47.349
You record the speech,
uh, we move down to PEOC.

12:47.350 --> 12:49.977
And when it's time, board Marine One
to Joint Base Andrews.

12:49.978 --> 12:52.521
- After that, I don't know.
- Are we going somewhere?

12:52.522 --> 12:54.649
- Sir, if I may, I just need a word.
- Okay.

13:00.530 --> 13:02.572
<i>We now take it
to our colleague Rebecca</i>

13:02.573 --> 13:06.285
<i>in Jakarta right now, where the wave
is due to hit at any moment.</i>

13:06.286 --> 13:08.328
<i>- Is that correct?
- That is correct, Bob.</i>

13:08.329 --> 13:10.372
<i>What you can't see is the water line,</i>

13:10.373 --> 13:12.374
<i>which is just beyond the city lights,</i>

13:12.375 --> 13:15.335
<i>has receded well over
three miles out to sea.</i>

13:15.336 --> 13:17.546
<i>You think that's a safe place
for you to be?</i>

13:17.547 --> 13:19.131
<i>We're on top of a 20-story building</i>

13:19.132 --> 13:20.882
<i>on the north shore of the island,
so we should--</i>

13:22.427 --> 13:24.261
-  <i>Oh, my God.
-  Oh, wow.</i>

13:24.262 --> 13:26.430
-  <i>You okay?
-  Oh!</i>

13:26.431 --> 13:28.307
<i>I don't know if you can hear that.</i>

13:28.308 --> 13:31.852
<i>We just got hit with a massive
high-pressure sound wave</i>

13:31.853 --> 13:35.564
<i>that has been preceding the tsunami
and wreaking havoc with air traffic</i>

13:35.565 --> 13:37.441
<i>throughout the southern hemisphere.</i>

13:38.818 --> 13:43.156
<i>It's quite painful, and...</i>

13:45.158 --> 13:46.242
<i>What?</i>

13:48.870 --> 13:49.953
What's going on?

13:49.954 --> 13:52.123
<i>What is that?</i>

13:52.832 --> 13:55.083
<i>Oh, my God!
Get away from the edge!</i>

13:55.084 --> 13:58.170
<i>Get away from...</i>

14:01.591 --> 14:03.508
<i>Did we just-- did we just lose her?</i>

14:03.509 --> 14:05.511
-  My God.
-  <i>We lost Rebecca.</i>

14:07.889 --> 14:09.306
<i>Can we get back to her?</i>

14:09.307 --> 14:11.349
<i>Can we get back to her?</i>

14:11.350 --> 14:13.268
- What's happening?
-  <i>Daddy, what's going on?</i>

14:13.269 --> 14:14.936
<i>They're moving a few of us
to another room.</i>

14:14.937 --> 14:16.354
<i>I think the president's kid.</i>

14:16.355 --> 14:17.731
Good. Is James with you?

14:17.732 --> 14:18.899
-  <i>Yeah.
- Good.</i>

14:18.900 --> 14:20.734
He is not to leave your sight,
do you understand me?

14:20.735 --> 14:22.027
- This is not a game.
-  <i>Okay.</i>

14:22.028 --> 14:23.111
You do not let go of his hand,

14:23.112 --> 14:25.489
and you do not lose sight
of Jeremy Bradford, promise me.

14:25.490 --> 14:27.784
<i>I promise. Where's Mom?</i>

14:28.451 --> 14:31.078
- I'm working on that.
<i>-  Daddy, people are freaking out.</i>

14:31.079 --> 14:33.288
<i>Mrs. Johnson fell in the stairs,
and I don't think she's okay.</i>

14:33.289 --> 14:36.041
Hey, listen to me. There's a plan.

14:36.042 --> 14:38.293
You're gonna be fine,
they're gonna take you to an airport,

14:38.294 --> 14:40.378
I'll see you there. So will Mom, okay?

14:40.379 --> 14:43.131
Shit.

14:43.132 --> 14:44.300
A plan?

14:45.051 --> 14:46.301
What airport? What do you know?

14:46.302 --> 14:48.261
- Have you talked to Cal?
- A little.

14:48.262 --> 14:50.472
- More soon, okay? Ryan!
- Xavier.

14:50.473 --> 14:51.932
Ryan!

14:51.933 --> 14:53.768
-  Xavier?
- Head in the game, man.

14:54.852 --> 14:55.936
Guard the door.

14:55.937 --> 14:58.147
[on TV] <i>The scale of this case
is much greater--</i>

14:58.856 --> 15:00.816
"Remain calm,
'cause the tsunami moves fast,

15:00.817 --> 15:02.109
